#. <section class="sutta" id="sn3.15"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.15:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.15:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. Childless"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.15:0.3"
msgid "15. Dutiyasaṅgāmasutta"
msgstr "15. Battle (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.84"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.190"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.15:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā "
"rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ abbhuyyāsi yena kāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha mobilized an army of four "
"divisions and marched to Kāsi to attack King Pasenadi of Kosala."

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.2"
msgid "Assosi kho rājā pasenadi kosalo:"
msgstr "When King Pasenadi heard of this,"

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.3"
msgid ""
"“rājā kira māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā "
"mamaṃ abbhuyyāto yena kāsī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā rājānaṃ "
"māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ paccuyyāsi yena kāsi."
msgstr ""
"he mobilized an army of four divisions and marched to Kāsi to defend it "
"against Ajātasattu."

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā ca māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto rājā ca pasenadi kosalo "
"saṅgāmesuṃ."
msgstr "Then the two kings met in battle."

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.6"
msgid ""
"Tasmiṃ kho pana saṅgāme rājā pasenadi kosalo rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ "
"vedehiputtaṃ parājesi, jīvaggāhañca naṃ aggahesi."
msgstr "And in that battle Pasenadi defeated Ajātasattu and captured him alive."

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho rañño pasenadissa kosalassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi thought:"

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.8"
msgid ""
"“kiñcāpi kho myāyaṃ rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto adubbhantassa "
"dubbhati, atha ca pana me bhāgineyyo hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Even though I’ve never betrayed this King Ajātasattu, he betrayed me. "
"Still, he is my nephew."

# I don’t think BB’s “confiscated” can work. What does it mean, Pasenadi marched home with all Ajatasattu’s troops? I don’t think so. Normally pariyadiyati means overpowered, mastered, vanquished, and so it means here.
#. VAR: osajjeyyan”ti → ossajjeyyanti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn3.15:1.9"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ rañño māgadhassa ajātasattuno vedehiputtassa sabbaṃ hatthikāyaṃ "
"pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ assakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ rathakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā "
"sabbaṃ pattikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā jīvantameva naṃ osajjeyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Now that I’ve vanquished all of Ajātasattu’s elephant troops, cavalry, "
"chariots, and infantry, why don’t I let him loose with just his life?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: osajji → ossajji (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn3.15:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo rañño māgadhassa ajātasattuno vedehiputtassa "
"sabbaṃ hatthikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ assakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ "
"rathakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ pattikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā jīvantameva naṃ "
"osajji."
msgstr "And that’s what he did."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.15:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisiṃsu."
msgstr "Then several mendicants …"

msgctxt "sn3.15:3.2"
msgid ""
"Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "told the Buddha what had happened."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.85"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.192"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.15:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bhante, rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ "
"sannayhitvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ abbhuyyāsi yena kāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.2"
msgid "Assosi kho, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.3"
msgid ""
"‘rājā kira māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā "
"mamaṃ abbhuyyāto yena kāsī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā "
"rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ paccuyyāsi yena kāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, rājā ca māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto rājā ca pasenadi "
"kosalo saṅgāmesuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.6"
msgid ""
"Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhante, saṅgāme rājā pasenadi kosalo rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ "
"ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ parājesi, jīvaggāhañca naṃ aggahesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.7"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.8"
msgid ""
"‘kiñcāpi kho myāyaṃ rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto adubbhantassa "
"dubbhati, atha ca pana me bhāgineyyo hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.9"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ rañño māgadhassa ajātasattuno vedehiputtassa sabbaṃ hatthikāyaṃ "
"pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ assakāyaṃ sabbaṃ rathakāyaṃ sabbaṃ pattikāyaṃ "
"pariyādiyitvā jīvantameva naṃ osajjeyyan’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.15:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Atha kho, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo rañño māgadhassa ajātasattuno "
"vedehiputtassa sabbaṃ hatthikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ assakāyaṃ "
"pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ rathakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ pattikāyaṃ "
"pariyādiyitvā jīvantameva naṃ osajjī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.15:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imā gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha recited these "
"verses:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.193"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.15:7.1"
msgid "“Vilumpateva puriso,"
msgstr "“A man goes on plundering"

# This and AN 10.177 seem to be the only occurrences of this verb in the EBTs, apart from the causative form in DN 15.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:7.2"
msgid "yāvassa upakappati;"
msgstr "as long as it serves his ends."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:7.3"
msgid "Yadā caññe vilumpanti,"
msgstr "But as soon as others plunder him,"

# See BB for this line.
#. <br>
#. VAR: viluppati → vilumpati (si, s1-3, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn3.15:7.4"
msgid "so vilutto viluppati."
msgstr "the plunderer is plundered."

# The use of thana here is obscure; BB has fortuneis on his side. I relate it to use the use of thana as “possible”, i.e. they can do it, i.e. they can get away with it.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.15:8.1"
msgid "Ṭhānañhi maññati bālo,"
msgstr "For the fool thinks they’ve got away with it"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:8.2"
msgid "yāva pāpaṃ na paccati;"
msgstr "as long as the wickedness doesn’t ripen."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:8.3"
msgid "Yadā ca paccati pāpaṃ,"
msgstr "But when the wickedness ripens,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:8.4"
msgid "atha dukkhaṃ nigacchati."
msgstr "they fall into suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
#. VAR: labhati → labhati hantā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.1"
msgid "Hantā labhati hantāraṃ,"
msgstr "A killer creates a killer;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.2"
msgid "jetāraṃ labhate jayaṃ;"
msgstr "a conqueror creates a conqueror;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.3"
msgid "Akkosako ca akkosaṃ,"
msgstr "an abuser creates abuse,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.4"
msgid "rosetārañca rosako;"
msgstr "and a bully creates a bully."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.5"
msgid "Atha kammavivaṭṭena,"
msgstr "And so as deeds unfold"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.6"
msgid "so vilutto viluppatī”ti."
msgstr "the plunderer is plundered.”"
